article.description: — Justin Hill registered 18 points as Longwood edged past Radford 71-66 on Wednesday night.
article.headline: Hill scores 18 to carry Longwood over Radford 71-66
article.linkText: Hill scores 18 to carry Longwood over Radford 71-66
article.story: FARMVILLE, Va. -- — Justin Hill registered 18 points as Longwood edged past Radford 71-66 on Wednesday night. Jesper Granlund had 14 points for Longwood (22-6, 14-1 Big South Conference), which earned its fourth consecutive win. Isaiah Wilkins added 10 points. Rashun Williams and Josiah Jeffers had 17 points apiece for the Highlanders (10-17, 6-9). Artese Stapleton had six assists. The Lancers improve to 2-0 against the Highlanders this season. Longwood defeated Radford 83-75 on Jan. 12. ------ For more AP college basketball coverage: https://apnews.com/hub/college-basketball and http://twitter.com/AP--Top25 ------ This was generated by Automated Insights, http://www.automatedinsights.com/ap, using data from STATS LLC, https://www.stats.com
